RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 14 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON THREE RACES IN 2022 - 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race at a mile or over since May 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GAGOOTS was unhurried early and raced far back along the inside, advanced to the second turn, swung wide entering the stretch, closed willingly and wore down his rivals to get up late. BEHAVIN MYSELF bobbled slightly at the start, set a pressured pace, swung out on the turn, drew clear, led to deep stretch and was outfinished in a good effort. WHERE'D THE DAY GO settled off the pace, advanced to the turn, shifted out, bid, had little left, hung late and held for show. KRAMDEN raced in the back, finished well and gained late. PISTOL BOX was unhurried early, saved ground, lacked a stretch response under mild urging and did not threaten. BLURT pressed the pace to the second turn, fell back, leveled off and steadily faded through the stretch.
